[SN]TITLE[SN]
Schools' Cup semi-final: RBAI 27-19 Ballymena Academy

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Schools' Cup holders RBAI are through to the St Patrick's Day decider thanks to a 27-19 win over Ballymena Academy at Kingspan Stadium on Monday.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
David Forsythe's try put Ballymena ahead before their Belfast opponents hit back with tries from David Whitten, Conor Field and Michael Lowry.
RBAI led 19-7 at the break and Mark Keane added their fourth try before Ballymena staged a comeback.
Mark Thompson and Christopher McLeister went over but RBAI held on to win.
RBAI will play the winners of Tuesday's other semi-final between Campbell College and Dalriada.
